There's also this idea of incremental lists and an incremental list means that it increments across it.

00:45:28.560 --> 00:45:33.520
So you might have like three or four bullet points and rather than displaying them all at once

00:45:33.520 --> 00:45:38.159
you can actually have them be incremental where it'll show bullet point one, then you click an

00:45:38.159 --> 00:45:43.679
arrow, bullet point two, click the arrow, bullet point three, and so on. So that you can actually walk

00:45:43.679 --> 00:45:48.719
through your slides like I'm doing today as opposed to them all showing up at one time.

00:45:49.679 --> 00:45:52.719
So you can do this from the YAML header with incremental equals true

00:45:53.919 --> 00:46:00.239
or you can turn it on and off via fence divs. So I might have something like this where again I use

00:46:00.239 --> 00:46:07.040
three colons to start, three colons to end, and then I have an dot incremental class and this will

00:46:07.040 --> 00:46:12.479
work across any of the presentation formats and it'll say first Howard sleeps and then the next

00:46:12.479 --> 00:46:17.679
one Howard sprints. He's always sleeping or running around in terms of he's an active dog or he's a

00:46:17.679 --> 00:46:23.280
very sleepy dog. But you can walk through the different parts of your presentation and control

00:46:23.280 --> 00:46:31.199
the overall structure in this way. You can also turn off incremental. So let's say that you had

00:46:31.199 --> 00:46:36.239
incremental equals true and you want to say that well you know I want to say that Howard eats and

00:46:36.239 --> 00:46:39.919
then he sleeps. Like that's kind of one thought that I'm putting together even though it's

00:46:39.919 --> 00:46:44.800
it's two different bullet points. So if he eats he's immediately going to go take a nap. He's not

00:46:44.800 --> 00:46:49.919
going to go run around after that. So you can turn on or turn off these incremental lists from the

00:46:49.919 --> 00:46:56.080
YAML or from Pandoc fence divs with the dot incremental or non-incremental classes.

00:46:58.719 --> 00:47:03.600
