00:47:03.600 --> 00:47:09.520
right columns or how those appear. This one's a bit more complex in terms you have what's called

00:47:09.520 --> 00:47:16.159
a dot columns class first and you might notice I have four colons here at the start and four

00:47:16.159 --> 00:47:22.879
colons at the bottom. This allows me to nest additional fence divs within that kind of parent

00:47:22.879 --> 00:47:29.439
div. So overall I have a dot columns class and then I'm creating two or more columns that I want

00:47:29.439 --> 00:47:35.919
to create within it. So within the dot columns class I create another three colons with a dot

00:47:35.919 --> 00:47:42.159
column and I can control the width so you know make it 50 50 or 40 60 or whatever kind of

00:47:42.159 --> 00:47:48.719
percentage I want from left and right. And then I'm also using reveal js's dot fragment class

00:47:48.719 --> 00:47:53.840
that allows me to display the content on the left first and then display the content on the right

00:47:53.840 --> 00:48:02.000
after that's done. So you can kind of build off of these classes and brackets and fence divs together

00:48:02.000 --> 00:48:05.040
and overall structure your document across different formats.

